Data words uses in function
HMI_CMD, dw X - command word from SCADA Bit 0 = auto Bit 1 = Manuel deactivate Bit 2 = Manuel activate Bit 3 = Locate Bit 4 = SV_2 Selection Bit Bit 5 = SV_3 Selection Bit Bit 6 = spare
HMI_INFO, dw X - info word to SCADA Bit 0 = activated Bit 1 = changing Bit 2 = faulty Bit 3 = auto_man, Manual = 1 Bit 4 = man_on_off Bit 5 = Reset_FB Bit 6 = ManualSelected Bit 7 = Set_FB Bit 8 = Locate Active Bit 9 = TrippedInd Bit 10 = IsolatedInd Bit 11 = VSD_Fault Bit 12 = VSD_Alarm Bit 13 = sv_3Activated Bit 14 = fb_error - Alarm feedback error Bit 15 = sv_2Activated
Error status 0 (Everything is OK) 16 (Sensor target missing (#16)) 17 (Setup prerequisite issue (#17)) 18 (Pneumatic part issue (#18)) 19 (Seat lift sensor issue (#19)) 20 (Position not reached (#20)) 21 (Unexpected movement (#21)) 22 (Seat-lift sensor missing (#22)) 23 (Pilot valve 1 missing (#23)) 24 (Pilot valve 2 missing (#24)) 25 (Pilot valve 3 missing (#25)) 26 (Interlock active (#26)) 27 (Output short circuit (#27)) 28 (Setup aborted (#28)) 29 (Blocked button (#29)) 30 (Communication failure (#30)) 31 (Safety stop active (#31))
